The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for planar graphs, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The use of BC trees and SPQR trees also suggests cs.GT (Graph Theory) as a possible category. The paper also discusses a biased heavy-path decomposition, which is a technique used in algorithmic graph theory and may suggest categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
